AN ACT relating to governmental entities; requiring certain units of government of
this State to accept certain forms of payment; and providing other
matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 This bill : (1) requires, with certain exceptions, each officer, agency, branch, board,
2 commission, department, division, bureau, district, city, county or other political subdivision
3 or unit of government of this State to accept from a business entity as payment for any fee, tax
4 or other debt, payment by debit card, credit card, check or electronic transfer of money [.] ;
5 and (2) authorizes such a governmental agency, at its discretion, to accept payment by
6 other methods, including, without limitation, cash or money order.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 237 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
2 section to read as follows:
3 1. Except as otherwise provided in subsection [2,] 3, each governmental
4 agency shall accept from a business entity as payment for any fee, tax or other
5 debt to the governmental agency payment by debit card, credit card, check or
6 electronic transfer of money.
7 2. In addition to the methods of payment which a governmental agency is
8 required by subsection 1 to accept from a business entity as payment for any fee,
9 tax or other debt to the governmental agency, a governmental agency may, at its
10 discretion, accept payment by other methods, including, without limitation, cash
11 or money order.
12 3. The provisions of subsection 1 do not apply to payments made:
13 (a) Pursuant to NRS 353.1467;
14 (b) To the Department of Taxation pursuant to paragraph (b) of subsection 1
15 of NRS 360A.040;
16 (c) To the Cannabis Compliance Board;

